                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.717,
                                "byte_start": 92081,
                                "byte_stop": 126981,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in United States Railroad Retirement Board against Fritz will be announced by Mr. Justice Rehnquist."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.717,
                        "stop": 217.852,
                        "byte_start": 126981,
                        "byte_stop": 963526,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15141,
                            "name": "William H. Rehnquist",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_h_rehnquist",
                            "last_name": "Rehnquist",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2787,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 63612000,
                                    "date_end": 528094800,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2787"
                                },
                                {
                                    "id": 2788,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 1125723600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2788"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32786,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 46923,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_rehnquist.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12293,
                            "identifier": "william_h_rehnquist"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.717,
                                "stop": 26.699,
                                "byte_start": 126981,
                                "byte_stop": 198974,
                                "text": "In this case, the United States District Court for the Southern District of Indiana held unconstitutional a section of the Railroad Retirement Act of 1974 and the United States Railroad Retirement Board has appealed directly to this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.699,
                                "stop": 35.805,
                                "byte_start": 198974,
                                "byte_stop": 235337,
                                "text": "The 1974 Act fundamentally restructured the railroad retirements system by eliminating certain retirement benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.805,
                                "stop": 54.027,
                                "byte_start": 235337,
                                "byte_stop": 308270,
                                "text": "Under the earlier system of person who worked for both railroads and nonrailroads and who qualified for both railroad retirement benefits and Social Security benefits was entitled to receive retirement benefit from both systems and an accompanying windfall benefit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.027,
                                "stop": 68.94,
                                "byte_start": 308270,
                                "byte_stop": 367934,
                                "text": "In 1974, Congress determined that the payment of these windfall benefits threatened the financial solvency of the railroad retirement system and decided to eliminate the benefits for a certain classes of employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.94,
                                "stop": 99.252,
                                "byte_start": 367934,
                                "byte_stop": 489142,
                                "text": "Thus, under Section 231 of the Act, some classes of employees such as those who had already retired or those who had not yet retired but who had 25 years of railroad experience continued to receive benefits under the old system and employees who were actually employed in the railroad industry in 1974 could have also received the windfall benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.252,
                                "stop": 111.733,
                                "byte_start": 489142,
                                "byte_stop": 539088,
                                "text": "But because appellee, Fritz, and his class members were not employed in the railroad industry in 1974, they failed to qualify for the old windfall benefit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.733,
                                "stop": 126.657,
                                "byte_start": 539088,
                                "byte_stop": 598752,
                                "text": "Fritz thus brought suit claiming that Section 231 was unconstitutional under the Due Process Clause of the Fifth Amendment because it irrationally distinguished between classes of employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.657,
                                "stop": 138.301,
                                "byte_start": 598752,
                                "byte_stop": 645354,
                                "text": "Fritz argued that it was arbitrary of Congress to deprive him of -- his benefits simply because he was not active in the railroad industry in 1974."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.301,
                                "stop": 144.448,
                                "byte_start": 645354,
                                "byte_stop": 669910,
                                "text": "The District Court agreed with Fritz and held Section 231 unconstitutional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.448,
                                "stop": 157.233,
                                "byte_start": 669910,
                                "byte_stop": 721110,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Court today, we reverse the judgment of the District Court and find that Congress\u0027 action in excluding Fritz and his class members was not irrational or arbitrary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.233,
                                "stop": 166.843,
                                "byte_start": 721110,
                                "byte_stop": 759457,
                                "text": "This Court has judicially deferred to the wisdom of the Congress\u2019 welfare -- Congress\u2019 judgment and social welfare o0r economic legislation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.843,
                                "stop": 181.517,
                                "byte_start": 759457,
                                "byte_stop": 818181,
                                "text": "We will not strike down the act of Congress simply because we deem it unwise or would have drawn or cut off benefits in -- at some other point than Congress did."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.517,
                                "stop": 187.279,
                                "byte_start": 818181,
                                "byte_stop": 841273,
                                "text": "In this case, Congress could have eliminated all retirement benefits if it\u0027s so desired."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.279,
                                "stop": 201.583,
                                "byte_start": 841273,
                                "byte_stop": 898429,
                                "text": "The classification of employees here is not arbitrary because Congress concluded that employees other than Fritz had a greater equitable claim for the windfall benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.583,
                                "stop": 205.77,
                                "byte_start": 898429,
                                "byte_stop": 915252,
                                "text": "The judgment of the District Court is accordingly reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.77,
                                "stop": 211.104,
                                "byte_start": 915252,
                                "byte_stop": 936568,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stevens has filed a separate opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.104,
                                "stop": 217.852,
                                "byte_start": 936568,
                                "byte_stop": 963526,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Brennan whom Mr. Justice Marshall joins has filed an opinion in dissent."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
